svg.text: 5.6 Million acres in SENDDs region is devoted to agriculture, with a county average of 350,871 acres

The 2017 data also shows that since 2012, agricultural expenses increased throughout the region while income and net cash largely decreased. Government payments also increased during that time with the average farm receiving $18,873. This may be an unsustainable model for agriculture. Commodity prices drive local economies, please see Economic Trends section for more information
